<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<title>FabCLI — Third-Party Licenses</title>
<style>
  body { font: 14px/1.5 -apple-system, "Segoe UI", sans-serif; max-width: 920px; margin: 2em auto; padding: 0 1em; color: #222; }
  h1 { border-bottom: 2px solid #444; padding-bottom: 0.3em; }
  h2 { margin-top: 2em; padding: 0.3em 0.5em; background: #f3f3f3; border-left: 4px solid #888; font-size: 1.1em; }
  .crates { color: #444; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0 1em; }
  .crates a { margin-right: 0.4em; }
  pre { background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 1em; overflow-x: auto; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 12px; }
  .toc { columns: 2; }
  .toc li { break-inside: avoid; }
  .note { color: #666; font-size: 0.85em; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.5em; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>FabCLI — Third-Party Licenses</h1>
<p>
FabCLI is licensed under
<a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html">GNU GPL v3.0 or later</a>.
The binary is built by linking the dependencies listed below; their
licenses (mostly MIT and Apache-2.0) require attribution preservation,
which this document provides.
</p>
<p class="note">
Licenses are grouped by SPDX identifier. Each section lists every
crate that ships under that license, followed by one canonical copy
of the license text. Per-crate copyright lines are preserved in the
crate&rsquo;s own repository, linked from the crate name.
</p>
<h2>Index</h2>
<ul class="toc">
{{#each overview}}
  <li><a href="#{{id}}">{{name}}</a> &mdash; {{count}} crate(s)</li>
{{/each}}
</ul>
{{#each overview}}
<h2 id="{{id}}">{{name}}</h2>
<div class="crates">Used by {{count}} crate(s):
{{#each indices}}
  {{#with (lookup ../../licenses this)}}
    {{#each used_by}}
      <a href="{{this.crate.repository}}">{{this.crate.name}} {{this.crate.version}}</a>
    {{/each}}
  {{/with}}
{{/each}}
</div>
{{#with (lookup ../licenses (lookup indices 0))}}
<pre>{{text}}</pre>
{{/with}}
{{/each}}
</body>
</html>
